'''Deveron Fonville''' (born 16 May 2003) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a defender for [[Eredivisie]] club [[NEC Nijmegen]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].

==Club career==
He is from [[Nieuwegein]] and has time playing in the youth academies of [[PSV Eindhoven]] and [[FC Utrecht]]. He made his debut in the [[Eerste Divisie]] for [[Jong FC Utrecht]] as a substitute against [[FC Volendam]] on 4 February 2022. Persistent injuries caused him to miss a year of football and he returned to the game at [[USV Hercules]].<ref>{{cite web|website=ad.nl|date=13 Sep 2025|title= Brother, teammate and former coach about IJsselstein's 'growing diamond' Deveron Fonville: 'He has extraordinary qualities' |accessdate=14 Nov 2025|url=https://www.ad.nl/ijsselstein/broer-ploeggenoot-en-oud-trainer-over-ijsselsteinse-groeibriljant-deveron-fonville-hij-heeft-buitengewone-kwaliteiten~a97480b3/?cb=4cdaba3a-833b-4422-8c46-d8b2530b70f9&auth_rd=1}}</ref>

Having played amateur football for [[IJsselmeervogels]] in the 2024–25 season, he signed for [[FC Dordrecht]] back in the Eerste Divisie ahead of the 2025–26 season.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.ad.nl/regiosport-dordrecht/deveron-fonville-ontpopt-zich-tot-surprise-bij-fc-dordrecht-verschil-qua-tempo-en-conditie-is-wel-groot~a3f1b5be/|website=ad.nl|accessdate=14 Nov 2025|title= Deveron Fonville is proving to be a surprise at FC Dordrecht: "The difference in pace and fitness is quite significant."|date=25 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/nieuws/1315047/eredivisie-clubs-vechten-om-dordrecht-revelatie-fonville.html|website=Voetbal primeur.nl|accessdate=14 Nov 2025|title= Remarkable rise: Eredivisie clubs fight for revelation who has just turned professional|date=July 28, 2025}}</ref> Playing for Dordrecht under manager [[Dirk Kuyt]], he made his debut in a 1–0 win over [[SC Cambuur]] on 8 August 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://dordtcentraal.nl/actueel/vernieuwd-fc-dordrecht-zet-onder-kuyt-thuisreeks-voort-goede-indruk-achtergelaten-bij-vriend-en-vijand/ |date=12 August 2025|title = A revamped FC Dordrecht continues its home run under Kuyt: "Left a good impression on friend and foe alike."|accessdate=30 December 2025|website= dordtcentraal.nl}}</ref>

Having impressed in four games for Dordrecht, Fonville joined [[Eredivisie]] club [[NEC Nijmegen]] in September 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.voetbalzone.nl/nieuws/voormalig-psv-jeugdspeler-hoopt-op-debuut-tegen-psv-na-twee-maanden-kwam-nec/blt62a6a7e515b4cf5d |title= Former PSV youth player hopes for debut against PSV: 'NEC came after two months' |website= voetbalzone |date=11 Sep 2025|accessdate=14 November 2025}}</ref> He made his debut in the Eredivisie against PSV Eindhoven on 13 September 2025, in a 5–3 home defeat.<ref>{{cite web|title=NEC VS. PSV 3-5|date=13 Sep 2025|url= https://www.soccerway.com/match/nijmegen-nRluRF0T/psv-M9UEHJWi/summary/lineups/?mid=WMmgIlZ7|website=Soccerway|accessdate=14 Nov 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
He was called-up to the [[Curaçao national football team]] for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF third round#Group B|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Bermuda national football team|Bermuda]] and [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]] on 13 and 18 November 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.gelderlander.nl/nec/deveron-fonville-heeft-een-unieke-route-afgelegd-richting-nec-ik-moest-opeens-verder-kijken-dan-voetbal~ae1d1e4d/?referrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2F|website=Gelderlander.nl|accessdate=14 Nov 2025|title= Deveron Fonville took a unique path to NEC: "I suddenly had to look beyond football."|date=12 Nov 2025}}</ref>

